      "data": {
        "summary": "CVE-2024-45491 is a CRITICAL integer overflow (CWE-190) in libexpat before 2.6.3. The flaw in dtdCopy() within xmlparse.c allows an integer overflow for nDefaultAtts on 32-bit platforms, potentially enabling memory corruption or remote code execution. The fix is available in libexpat 2.6.3.",
        "severity": "critical",
        "confidence": "high",
        "recommended_action": "Upgrade libexpat to 2.6.3+. Not in CISA KEV; no public exploit confirmed. CVSS 9.8 Critical, EPSS 62nd percentile (1.13%). SSVC: Track* \u2014 patch within standard timelines, especially on 32-bit systems. Apply exploit protections (ASLR, stack canaries) and sandbox XML-parsing components as interim measures. Check downstream embedders (Python, PHP, Apache httpd) for their own updates.",
